	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>FARID</b> [ Tue Nov 26, 2013 9:22 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: My MMC3 conversion pack</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Putting more games inside of a single cartridge needs bigger EPROMs!<br />I don't like SMD so it is out of question!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" /> <br />Bigger EPROMs can't fit inside of a FC cartridge<br />7 in 1 Mario cartridge needs these chips so far :<br />27C080 --&gt; PRG-ROM<br />6264 --&gt; PRG-RAM<br />27C080 --&gt; CHR-ROM<br />AX5202P --&gt; MMC3<br />74xx174 --&gt; Latch<br />74xx238 --&gt; Decoder<br />74xx4053 --&gt; Game Size control<br /><br />And for bits of register :<br />D0 --&gt; A19 [PRG+CHR]<br />D1 --&gt; A18 [PRG+CHR]<br />D2 --&gt; A17 [PRG+CHR]<br />D3 --&gt; Size [0:256 1:128] <br />D4 --&gt; PRG-RAM [0:En 1:Dis]<br />D5 --&gt; Latch [0:En 1:Dis]

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
